'''Alexander Grossmann''' (Croatian: ''Aleksander Grossmann''; born 5 August 1930) is a [[Croatia]]n-[[France|French]] [[physicist]] at the [[Université de la Méditerranée Aix-Marseille II]] in [[Luminy]] campus who did pioneering work on [[wavelet]] analysis with [[Jean Morlet]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cmi.univ-mrs.fr/~torresan/HASSIP/hassipbib/Author/GROSSMANN-A.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2009-12-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716113349/http://www.cmi.univ-mrs.fr/~torresan/HASSIP/hassipbib/Author/GROSSMANN-A.html |archive-date=2011-07-16 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>http://stat.genopole.cnrs.fr/publications?author=grossmann{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

