'''Bledisloe Glacier''' ({{Coord|81|22|S|156|21|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] flowing north west between [[All-Blacks Nunataks]] and [[Wallabies Nunataks]], west of the [[Churchill Mountains]]. It was named in association with the adjacent All-Blacks and Wallabies Nunataks, and specifically named after the [[Bledisloe Cup]], which is contested between the New Zealand and Australian [[rugby union]] teams, the [[All-Blacks]] and the [[Australia national rugby union team|Wallabies]].

